2.0 Transform data

This section transforms and enhance data in the slimmed down lowy_posting data frame. - it will add iso keys for countries - it will geo-code cities to add provisional latitude/longitude points for the lowy institute as is

2.1 Add country iso codes to data frame

-Set up empty lists and new data frame -cycle through all country names and call the countrycode() function defining sourcevar, destination, origin before appending the result to one of our empty lists

#Set up some blank objects

#iso encoded dataframe
lowy_posting_iso <- lowy_posting
#country_iso list [column 1]
iso_list_send_country <- c()
#post_country_iso list [column 3]
iso_list_post_country <- c()
#sending country column (1)
for(country in lowy_posting[1]){
  country_iso <- countrycode(
    #call the entry of 'Country' for the row_number currently being taken by for loop
    sourcevar = country, 
    #three letter iso code
    destination = "genc3c", 
    #based on english language names
    origin = "country.name")
  
  #add value to a list
  iso_list_send_country <- append(iso_list_send_country,country_iso)
}

#Post country column (3)
for(country in lowy_posting[3]){
  post_country_iso <- countrycode(
    #call the entry of 'Country' for the row_number currently being taken by for loop
    sourcevar = country, 
    #three letter iso code
    destination = "genc3c", 
    #based on english language names
    origin = "country.name")
  
  #add value to a list
  iso_list_post_country <- append(iso_list_post_country,post_country_iso)
}

Create function to visualise diplomatic postings by country

Virdis pallette reference used in mapview found here

#function that assumes 'send country' column is present
f_country_postings <- function(p_select_country,p_df){
  
  #Subset of dataframe for chosen country
  sub_df <- p_df[p_df$send_country == p_select_country,]
  
  #country layer taking sending related columns (1-4)
  country_layer <- sub_df[1,1:4]
  country_layer_sf <-
    st_as_sf(country_layer,coords=c("send_lon","send_lat"),crs = 4326)
  
  #posting layer taking posting related columns (5-)
  posting_layer <- sub_df[5:12]
  posting_layer_sf <-
    st_as_sf(posting_layer,coords=c("post_city_lon","post_city_lat"),crs = 4326)
  
  map <- 
    mapview(
      #spatial object
      posting_layer_sf,
      legend = FALSE,
      layer.name = paste(p_select_country, "diplomatic posts"),
      alpha.regions = 0.4,
      label = posting_layer$post_city_country,
      zcol = "post_country",
      col.regions = viridisLite::cividis
        #plasma
        
      )+ mapview(
      #spatial object
      country_layer_sf, 
      legend = FALSE,
      layer.name = paste(p_select_country, "point"),
      label = country_layer_sf$send_country,
      color = "red",
      alpha.regions = 0.4,
      col.regions = "red")
  return(map) 
}

#Create function out of above

f_exact_city_postings <- function(p_city_filter,p_df){
  
  ###Subset of dataframe for chosen country
  sub_city_df <- p_df[p_df$post_city == p_city_filter,]

  ###Geocode and save
  sub_city_df_dl <- mutate_geocode(sub_city_df, query2)

  #Save .csv file
  write.csv(sub_city_df_dl,paste("/cloud/project/Data/GoogleAPI/",p_city_filter,"geocoded.csv",sep = "_"), row.names = TRUE)
  
  #create spatial objects
  sub_city_sf <- 
    st_as_sf(sub_city_df_dl,coords=c("post_city_lon","post_city_lat"),crs = 4326)

  sub_city_geo_sf <-
    st_as_sf(sub_city_df_dl,coords=c("lon","lat"),crs = 4326)

  #City lat longs
  exact_map <- mapview(
      #spatial object
      sub_city_sf,
      legend = FALSE,
      layer.name = "City coordinates",
      alpha.regions = 0.4,
      label = sub_city_sf$post_city_country,
      cex = 10
      
      #Exact lat longs
      )+ mapview(
      #spatial object
      sub_city_geo_sf,
      legend = FALSE,
      layer.name = "Geocoded exact coordinates",
      label = sub_city_geo_sf$query2,
      color = "red",
      alpha.regions = 0.4,
      col.regions = "red",
      cex = 0.1)
  
  mapshot(exact_map, url = paste("/cloud/project/Data/MapFiles/",p_city_filter,"map.html",sep="_"))

  #return dl table,map
  return_list <- list(df = sub_city_df_dl,map = exact_map)
  return(return_list)
}
